Overview 
This Director, Software and Analytics will: 
Define and deliver a market leading, global, software platform for integrating the Costa Express portfolio of Autonomous Retail products into Costaâ€™s overall retail experience. 
Define and Deliver Costa US Digital applications to enable activation of Costa Express Autonomous Retail products within the larger Costa US Digital roadmap and supporting the timely deployment of Autonomous Retail platforms to the US Market. 
Drive the integration of Autonomous Retail data and operational systems with Costa Express Platform operational systems as well as market level consumer data analytics, reporting, and CRM capabilities. 
Key Tasks/Activities 
Organizational Management/People Development 
Clearly and consistently communicate business and product vistion to the Software and Data teams. 
Evaluation/assessments of competitors, technology and/or potential strategic partners/acquisition targets. 
Lead/Manage build vs. outsource vs. buy decisions. 
Lead selection of technical partners. 
Recruit and develop technical teams. 
Build a software development culture focused on delivery excellence within the context of the Costa values. 
Software Roadmap and Plan Development 
Set corporate innovation directions aligned with senior leadership 
Work cross-functionally with Engineering, Operations, Product, Finance, and R&D leaders to build the roadmap for the Software team and overall platform strategy. 
Represent Autonomous Retail software within Costa Platform, Market Regions and across broader Coca-Cola software initiatives. 
Software Delivery 
Drive software development across multiple teams, workstreams and phases to ensure delivery on time, on budget and to business objectives. 
Drive creation and operation of agile software development processes that align with overall Express platform product process. 
Drive development teams to consistently improve cycle times and overall product quality. 
Minimize technical risk by foreseeing, communicating and addressing obstacles proactively and aggressively. 
Data Delivery 
Drive integration of Autonomous Retail sales and telemetry data into existing/planned operational environments to support existing business functions. 
Push the current boundaries of the utilization of operation data to automate operational processes and minimize overall operating costs. 
Drive integration of consumer data from the Autonomous Retail platform with Costa Global consumer data strategies. 
Financial Planning & Management 
Build, justify, track and manage to Allocated Budget numbers for commitments across the team. 
Communicate and manage budgetary risks to Finance and Senior leadership team. 
Educational Requirements 
Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or other relevant Engineering field. 
